main event: A witness reported observing a small bright object in the sky for 10-12 seconds over Alexandria, Virginia.
interesting points: The object was described as bright and varied in the sky, seeming stationary,The witness had a clear view of the object as it passed overhead,There were no wings or propeller visible,The object was internally lit and made no noise during its flight,The estimated speed of the object was around 1,500 miles per hour.
sighted object: a small bright object in the sky
witness description: A person who observed the object around 11:30 P.M.
